On Mon, 10 Jun 2002, David & Susan Bell wrote:

> When I am changing oil, I fill the new filter with fresh oil which takes
> care of getting oil on the seal and the threads! The filter usually takes
> about .5 quart which I deduct from the 3.7 quarts that goes into the
> crankcase. This is how I was taught to do it many years ago and I have
> always done it since. Supposed to be better for the engine when you start up
> after the oil change. Any opinions?

An excellent idea, if the filter is installed open-end-up.  If installing
a remote filter, be sure to orient it this way!

George

